Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on parallel simulation of reservoir models on a supercomputer. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of an in-house black oil simulator. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance and scalability of the simulator. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of the simulator using MPI for communication. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is relevant as the paper focuses on simulation of reservoir models, which is a common application in computational engineering.
